Beginnings of IPv6 support

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

udp: initial ipv6 support

Basic IPv6 support, no logic, just plain raw IPv6 supported, optionally
with UDP payload.  Not fragment or routing support yet.

Useful for generating IPv6 multicast, e.g.,

    nemesis udo -c 1000 -i 1 -d eth0 -6 -S ff2e::42 -D ff02::42 -M 33:33:00:00:00:42
